value.value: A phyllome stomatal complex that is part of a carpel.
A phyllome stomatal complex (PO:0025215) that is part of a petal (PO:0009032).
A phyllome stomatal complex that is part of a sepal.
A phyllome stomatal complex that is part of a stamen.
A phyllome stomatal complex that is part of a tepal (PO:0009033).
A shoot apex that has as part a reproductive shoot apical meristem.
A shoot apex PO:0000037) that has as part a vegetative shoot apical meristem (PO:0008016).
A plant anatomical space that is the space between a shoot axis and a leaf, bract, or branch that branches from the shoot axis.
An axil that is the space between a shoot axis and a bract that branches from the shoot axis.
An axil that is the space between a shoot axis and a branch that branches from the shoot axis.
A portion of plant tissue consisting of four megaspores that remained joined together shortly after meiosis. One cell will give rise to a female gametophyte.

definition.value: Usually only one of the four megaspores develops and the other three die.

value.value: A cardinal organ part that is a part of a plant structure that splits apart when the structure dehisces.
A valve that is a part of a spore capsule that splits apart when the spore capsule dehisces.

definition.value: Found in bryophytes. A spore capsule may dehisce ongitudinally, forming evenely sized valves, or it may dehisce at the capsule annulus, forming the operculum, which is a specialized type of valve.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that forms the central axis of a plant structure such as a fruit (PO:0009001) or moss capsule (sporangium; PO:0025094).
A columella (PO:0025230) that forms the central axis of a spore capsule.

definition.value: Found in bryophytes.

value.value: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).

definition.value: This class is for tissues that only occur as part of an embryo.

value.value: A stomatal pore that is part of a phyllome stomatal complex.
A phyllome stomatal pore that is part of a leaf stomatal complex.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A guard cell that is part of a phyllome stomatal complex.
A phyllome guard cell that is part of a leaf stomatal complex.

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A petiole canal on the abaxial surface of a petiole.
A petiole canal on the adaxial surface of a petiole.

A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) that is part of an inflorescence (PO:0009049) and has as parts a second order inflorescence axis (PO:0006321) and any shoot axes (PO:0025029) and flowers (PO:0009046) that arise from it.

definition.value: This a sub-inflorescence that arises from the main inflorescence axis.

value.value: A reproductive shoot system that is part of an infructescence and has as parts a second order infructescence axis and any infructescence axes and fruits that arise from it.
A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is part of an infructescence (PO:0006342).
An infructescence axis (PO:0025242), which is a branch (PO:0025073) in an infructescence (PO:0006342), that develops from a higher order inflorescence axis (PO:0009081).

definition.value: A higher order infructescence axis is named according to its position in an infructescence (PO:0006342). Tenth order infructescence axis (PO:0025112) is the greatest specific infructescence axis (PO:0025242) order in the PO; when mapping annotations to an infructescence axis which is of an order higher than ten, or when order is ambiguous or unknown, annotate directly to higher order infructescence axis (PO:0025243).

value.value: An infructescence axis (PO:0025242), which is the primary or main axis of an infructescence (PO:0006342), that develops from a first order inflorescence axis (PO:0025104).
A phyllome that develops from a sepal and remains attached to a fruit at maturity.

definition.value: May be alive or dead at maturity.

value.value: A phyllome (PO:0006001) that develops from a tepal (PO:0009033) and remains attached to a fruit (PO:0009001) at maturity.

definition.value: May be alive or dead at maturity.

value.value: A phyllome that develops from a stamen and remains attached to a fruit at maturity.

definition.value: May be alive or dead at maturity.

value.value: A collective organ part structure that forms a cylindrical false stem composed concentric leaf sheaths.

definition.value: The peduncle later grows up through the pseudostem. Common in Musa species and some other monocots.

value.value: A portion of leaf epidermis (PO:0006016) that is part of a leaf sheath (PO:0020104).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A portion of leaf sheath epidermis (PO:0025249) that covers the abaxial/lower surface of a leaf sheath (PO:0020104).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A portion of leaf sheath epidermis (PO:0025249) that covers the adaxial/upper surface of a leaf sheath (PO:0020104).

definition.value: If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to vascular leaf (PO:0009025) or non-vascular leaf (PO:0025075), depending on the species. All annotations for angiosperms, gymnosperms, and pteridophytes should go to vascular leaf and all annotations for bryophytes should go to non-vascular leaf.

value.value: A higher order infructescence axis (PO:0025243) which arises from a sixth order infructescence axis (PO:0025116) and develops from a seventh order inflorescence axis (PO:0025108).
A higher order infructescence axis (PO:0025243) which arises from a seventh order infructescence axis (PO:0025252) and develops from an eighth order inflorescence axis (PO:0025109).
A higher order infructescence axis (PO:0025243) which arises from an eighth order infructescence axis (PO:0025253) and develops from a ninth order inflorescence axis (PO:0025110).
A higher order infructescence axis (PO:0025243) which arises from a ninth order infructescence axis (PO:0025254) and develops from a tenth order inflorescence axis (PO:0025111).

definition.value: Tenth order infructescence axis (PO:0025112) is the greatest specific infructescence axis (PO:0025242) order in the PO; when mapping annotations to an infructescence axis which is of an order higher than ten, or when order is ambiguous or unknown, annotate directly to higher order infructescence axis (PO:0025243).

value.value: A root elongation zone that is part of a lateral root tip.
A root elongation zone (PO:0025181) that is part of a primary root tip (PO:0000026).
A meristematic cell (PO:0004010) that is part of a portion of procambium (PO:0025275).
A portion of shoot procambium (PO:0025276) tissue that is part of a vascular leaf (PO:0009025).
A portion of shoot procambium that is part of a shoot apical meristem and gives rise to the primary vascular tissue of a shoot axis.
A ground tissue cell that is part of a portion of pericycle.
A septum (PO:0000030) that divides a multilocular plant ovary (PO:0009072).

definition.value: Found in species with syncarpous gynoecia (fused carpels). A plant ovary septum is derived from the fused walls of two adjacent carpels, while a replum (PO:0005016) develops from early contact of placental tissue from opposite sides of the plant ovary. Annotations for Arabidopsis should go under replum, not under plant ovary septum.

value.value: A plant anatomical space (PO:0025117) that is a cavity a reproductive structure.

definition.value: May be a cavity in a sporophyll, within several fused sporophylls, or within a sporangium. In many instances, the locules are filled with seeds or other plant structures.

value.value: A sporangium locule that is part of an anther and is a cavity within a single pollen sac or two or more fused pollen sacs.
A locule (PO:0025263) that is a cavity in a sporangium (PO:0025094) or several fused sporangia.

definition.value: May be filled with spores.

value.value: A locule (PO:0025263) that is a cavity in a plant ovary (PO:0009072).

definition.value: Generally contains at least one ovule. An ovary locule may be part of a single carpel, in the case of unicarpellate flowers. An ovary that is part of a syncarpous gynoecium may have multiple locules, or the anatomical spaces of multiple carpels may be fused to form a single locule.

value.value: A portion of fruit placenta tissue  (PO:0004535) that divides a fruit (PO:0009001) into two or more chambers and develops from a plant ovary replum (PO:0025272).

definition.value: A fruit replum develops from the ovary replum and has no suture line in its center, while a fruit septum (PO:0025262) develops from an ovary septum via the fusion of two adjacent ovary walls. Common in Brassicaceae. Annotations for Arabidopsis fruit should go here, and not under fruit septum. If you are annotating to this term, please add an additional annotation to the specific type of fruit (PO:0009001), such as achene fruit (PO:0030107), berry fruit (PO:0030108), capsule fruit (PO:0030091), caryopsis fruit (PO:0030104), drupe fruit (PO:0030103), follicle fruit (PO:0030105), legume fruit (PO:0030100), nut fruit (PO:0030102), samara fruit (PO:0030099), schizocarp fruit (PO:0030098), silique fruit (PO:0030106), or their subclasses, depending on the species.
